Query: 
Read all values and calculate a “median” from all values = statements. Put the commonalities at the beginning, evaluate the deviations in terms of their significance, and list them behind them. Explain all deviations of all datasets. In case no deviations of a dataset can be found, show the empty bracket [] as well. Don't supervise the existing results by your own insights. Don't optimize deviation results. 


